subSubSection.paragraph:
The 

Dromochorus

species have sometimes been treated as a distinct genus (
Guérin-Méneville, 1845
; 
Sallé, 1877
; 
Fleutiaux, 1892
; 
Casey, 1897
; 
Rivalier, 1954
, 
1963
, 
1971
; 
Johnson, 1991
; 
Wiesner, 1992
; 
Erwin & Pearson, 2008
; 
Bousquet, 2012
; 

Pearson 
et al.
, 2015

); or viewed to be a synonym of 

Cicindela

(e.g. 
LeConte, 1875
; 
Leng, 1902
; 
Harris, 1911
; 
Horn, 1915
; 
Harris & Leng, 1916
; 
Cazier, 1954
; 
Arnett, 1963
; 
Willis, 1968
; 
Bousquet & Larochelle, 1993
; 
Arnett & Thomas, 2000
), with some North American workers recognizing the taxon as a subgenus (
Boyd, 1982
; 
Freitag, 1999
). Despite the variety of treatments, justifications for different taxonomic ranks were almost never given.

